					Full Description



Straight Path Communications Inc., incorporated on April 4, 2013, is a communications asset company. The Company owns Straight Path Spectrum, Inc. (Straight Path Spectrum), Straight Path Ventures, LLC (Straight Path Ventures) and Straight Path IP Group, Inc. (Straight Path IP Group). The Company's segments include Straight Path Spectrum, Straight Path Ventures and Straight Path IP Group. Straight Path Spectrum's subsidiary, Straight Path Spectrum, LLC, holds, leases and markets a range of licensed commercial fixed and mobile wireless spectrum licenses.Straight Path SpectrumThe Company holds a range of licenses for fixed and mobile wireless spectrum in the United States. These include licenses in the 39 gigahertz (38.6-40 gigahertz) band and the 28 gigahertz (27.5-28.35 gigahertz) portion of the local multipoint distribution service (LMDS) band. The Company also holds licenses for fixed wireless spectrum in other parts of the LMDS band. The Company's spectrum is used primarily to provide fixed wireless services for existing Wireless Internet Service Providers (WISPs) and Mobile Network Operators (MNOs). MNOs use the Company's spectrum for macro cellular backhaul where fiber backhaul is not available or as a substitute for fiber. The Company's 39 gigahertz licenses comprise its primary spectrum holdings. As of July 31, 2016, the Company held 828 Economic Areas (EAs) licenses in the 39 gigahertz band that cover all 175 EAs in the United States. As of July 31, 2016, the Company also held 133 LMDS Basic Trading Area (BTA) licenses, including 16 licenses in the 27.5-28.35 gigahertz LMDS A1 band.The Company leases spectrum and provides related services for last mile, mid-mile, fixed access and backhaul applications to Internet service and telecommunications providers and other companies that operate fixed wireless networks and have the operational systems to support a network build-out. Fixed wireless operations in its bands can be deployed using point-to-point (PTP) or point-to-multipoint (PMP) installations. Straight Path Spectrum supports the commercialization of fifth generation (5G) millimeter wave technology.Straight Path VenturesThe Company's segment, Straight Path Ventures, is engaged in developing wireless technology. Straight Path Ventures is developing wireless technology primarily for 39 gigahertz at its Gigabit Mobility Lab in Plano, Texas.Straight Path IP GroupThe Straight Path IP Group's principal business is the acquisition, development, licensing and protection of intellectual property. The Straight Path IP Group owns intellectual property primarily related to communications over the Internet, and the licensing and other businesses related to this intellectual property.The Company competes with Level 3 Communications, Inc., NEON, Verizon, Comcast, Time Warner, XO Communications and AT&T.

» Full Overview of STRP.K







